You need to manually inject the trace context into RabbitMQ message headers on the publisher side and extract it on the consumer side. Here's the pattern:

**Service A (Publisher) — inject context:**

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current context into headers
DistributedContextPropagator.Current.Inject(
    activity, props.Headers, static (carrier, key, value) =>
    {
        if (carrier is IDictionary<string, object> h)
            h[key] = value;
    });

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Service B (Consumer) — extract context and link:**

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
var headers = ea.BasicProperties.Headers ?? new Dictionary<string, object>();

DistributedContextPropagator.Current.ExtractTraceIdAndState(
    headers,
    static (carrier, key) =>
    {
        if (carrier is IDictionary<string, object> h &&
            h.TryGetValue(key, out var val))
            return val is byte[] b ? System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(b) : val?.ToString();
        return null;
    },
    out var traceParent,
    out var traceState);

// Restore parent context
ActivityContext parentContext = default;
if (ActivityContext.TryParse(traceParent, traceState, out var parsed))
    parentContext = parsed;

using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
    "OrderEvent Process",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext);
```

**Key setup in `Program.cs` (both services):**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Why it doesn't work automatically:** RabbitMQ's .NET client has no built-in OpenTelemetry propagation (unlike HTTP where `HttpClient` does it for you). You must manually pass the `traceparent`/`tracestate` W3C headers through the message properties.

If you're using MassTransit or NServiceBus on top of RabbitMQ, both have built-in propagation — enable their diagnostic listeners instead of doing this manually.
